84:
SELECT DISTINCT t.name, s.District
FROM (
    SELECT AdmFName1 AS name FROM schools WHERE AdmFName1 IS NOT NULL
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName2 AS name FROM schools WHERE AdmFName2 IS NOT NULL
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName3 AS name FROM schools WHERE AdmFName3 IS NOT NULL
) t
JOIN schools s ON (t.name = s.AdmFName1 OR t.name = s.AdmFName2 OR t.name = s.AdmFName3)
WHERE t.name IN (
    SELECT name
    FROM (
        SELECT AdmFName1 AS name FROM schools WHERE AdmFName1 IS NOT NULL
        UNION ALL
        SELECT AdmFName2 AS name FROM schools WHERE AdmFName2 IS NOT NULL
        UNION ALL
        SELECT AdmFName3 AS name FROM schools WHERE AdmFName3 IS NOT NULL
    ) 
    GROUP BY name
    ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
    LIMIT 2
)
ORDER BY t.name, s.District

94:
SELECT 
    a.account_id,
    (SELECT MAX(d.A11) - MIN(d.A11) FROM district d) AS salary_gap
FROM client c
JOIN disp d ON c.client_id = d.client_id
JOIN account a ON d.account_id = a.account_id
WHERE c.gender = 'F'
AND c.birth_date = (
    SELECT birth_date 
    FROM client 
    WHERE gender = 'F' 
    ORDER BY birth_date ASC 
    LIMIT 1
)
AND c.district_id = (
    SELECT district_id 
    FROM client 
    WHERE gender = 'F' 
    AND birth_date = (
        SELECT birth_date 
        FROM client 
        WHERE gender = 'F' 
        ORDER BY birth_date ASC 
        LIMIT 1
    )
    ORDER BY district_id ASC
    LIMIT 1
)

ORDER BY

944:
SELECT 
    CAST((last_time_seconds - champion_time_seconds) AS REAL) / champion_time_seconds * 100 AS percentage_faster
FROM (
    SELECT 
        (SELECT 
            CASE 
                WHEN r.time LIKE '%:%' THEN 
                    CAST(SUBSTR(r.time, 1, INSTR(r.time, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60 + 
                    CAST(SUBSTR(r.time, INSTR(r.time, ':') + 1) AS REAL)
                ELSE CAST(r.time AS REAL)
            END
         FROM results r 
         JOIN races ra ON r.raceId = ra.raceId 
         WHERE ra.year = 2008 AND ra.name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND r.position = 1
        ) AS champion_time_seconds,
        (SELECT 
            CASE 
                WHEN r.time LIKE '%:%' THEN 
                    CAST(SUBSTR(r.time, 1, INSTR(r.time, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60 + 
                    CAST(SUBSTR(r.time, INSTR(r.time, ':') + 1) AS REAL)
                ELSE CAST(r.time AS REAL)
            END
         FROM results r 
         JOIN races ra ON r.raceId = ra.raceId 
         WHERE ra.year = 2008 AND ra.name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND r.time IS NOT NULL AND r.position IS NOT NULL
         ORDER BY r.position DESC LIMIT 1
        ) AS last_time_seconds
) 
WHERE champion_time_seconds IS NOT NULL AND last_time_seconds IS NOT NULL

    r.year,
    AVG(
        CASE 
            WHEN res.time LIKE '%:%.%' THEN
                CAST(SUBSTR(res.time, 1, INSTR(res.time, ':') - 1) AS INTEGER) * 60 +
                CAST(SUBSTR(res.time, INSTR(res.time, ':') + 1, INSTR(res.time, '.') - INSTR(res.time, ':') - 1) AS REAL) +
                CAST(SUBSTR(res.time, INSTR(res.time, '.') + 1) AS REAL) / 1000
            ELSE 0
        END
    ) AS avg_time_seconds
FROM 
    results res
    INNER JOIN races r ON res.raceId = r.raceId
    INNER JOIN status s ON res.statusId = s.statusId

    s.status = 'Finished'
    AND r.year < 1975

1481:
WITH min_consumption AS (
    SELECT c.Segment, MIN(y.Consumption) as min_cons
    FROM yearmonth y
    INNER JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
    WHERE y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    AND c.Currency = 'CZK'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
min_customers AS (
    SELECT y.CustomerID, c.Segment, y.Consumption
    FROM yearmonth y
    INNER JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
    INNER JOIN min_consumption mc ON c.Segment = mc.Segment AND y.Consumption = mc.min_cons
    WHERE y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    AND c.Currency = 'CZK'
),
segment_averages AS (
    SELECT Segment, AVG(Consumption) as avg_consumption
    FROM min_customers
    GROUP BY Segment
),
sme_avg AS (
    SELECT avg_consumption FROM segment_averages WHERE Segment = 'SME'
),
lam_avg AS (
    SELECT avg_consumption FROM segment_averages WHERE Segment = 'LAM'
),
kam_avg AS (
    SELECT avg_consumption FROM segment_averages WHERE Segment = 'KAM'
)
SELECT 
    (SELECT avg_consumption FROM sme_avg) - (SELECT avg_consumption FROM lam_avg) AS SME_LAM_diff,
    (SELECT avg_consumption FROM lam_avg) - (SELECT avg_consumption FROM kam_avg) AS LAM_KAM_diff,
    (SELECT avg_consumption FROM kam_avg) - (SELECT avg_consumption FROM sme_avg) AS KAM_SME_diff
1482:
SELECT 
    (SELECT Segment FROM (
        SELECT c.Segment, 
               ((SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) - 
                 SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END)) * 100.0 / 
                SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END)) as pct_change
        FROM yearmonth y 
        INNER JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID 
        WHERE SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013') 
          AND c.Currency = 'EUR'
          AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
        GROUP BY c.Segment
        HAVING SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) > 0
    ) ORDER BY pct_change DESC LIMIT 1) as biggest_increase_segment,
    (SELECT Segment FROM (
        SELECT c.Segment, 
               ((SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) - 
                 SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END)) * 100.0 / 
                SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END)) as pct_change
        FROM yearmonth y 
        INNER JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID 
        WHERE SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013') 
          AND c.Currency = 'EUR'
          AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
        GROUP BY c.Segment
        HAVING SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) > 0
    ) ORDER BY pct_change ASC LIMIT 1) as lowest_increase_segment
